{"title":"The Models for American Gothic","link":"https://kottke.org/24/06/the-models-for-american-gothic-1","date":1718969385000,"content":"\n        <p>In 1930, Iowa artist Grant Wood painted <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_gothic\">American Gothic</a>. The models he used for the painting were his sister Nan Wood Graham and his dentist, Byron McKeeby. Here they are next to the painting:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/american-gothic-models.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/american-gothic-models.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/american-gothic-models.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1000\" height=\"787\" alt=\"American Gothic Models\" /></p>\n\n<p>Wood made the painting after spotting a small house in Eldon, Iowa:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/american-gothic-house.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/american-gothic-house.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/american-gothic-house.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1000\" height=\"750\" alt=\"American Gothic House\" /></p>\n\n         <p><em>[This is a vintage post originally from Feb 2012.]</em></p>\n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/American%20Gothic\">American Gothic</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/art\">art</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Grant%20Wood\">Grant Wood</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/timeless%20posts\">timeless posts</a></p>\n\n        \n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"c90ea4eaa200f66c63e10c9a5d47f375ac93eda0ce26940633d4f1c2ae